heaviest_rainfall.status: 36.8mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 04 January 2025, marking an exceptional 37.2 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: The longest rain storm on record lasted 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

most_lightning.status: The most lightning activity recorded in a single day is 23, which occurred on 07 September 2025 (since our records began on 11 April 2025).

summary.description:
Today, a bit warmer for the feels like temperature (up 3.7°C) and outside temperature (up 2.9°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 9%) and rainfall (up 0.7 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in light levels (up 5443 lux), pressure (up 10 mbar), and cloud levels (up 608 m).

The past week and month had observable variation in light levels (up 9105 lux) and cloud levels (up 1012 m) when compared to today.
